==Coaches==

===Coaching changes===
The ACC entered the 2022 season with four new head football coaches:

* On November 16, 2021, Virginia Tech head coach [[Justin Fuente]] agreed to part ways with the program<ref>{{cite web |last1=Adelson |first1=Andrea |title=Justin Fuente out as Virginia Tech Hokies football coach |date=November 16, 2021|url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/32643652/justin-fuente-virginia-tech-hokies-football-coach |website=espn.com |publisher=ESPN |access-date=February 1, 2022}}</ref> and was replaced by [[Brent Pry]] on November 30, 2021.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Schlabach |first1=Mark |last2=Rittenberg|first2=Adam|date=November 30, 2021|title=Virginia Tech names Penn State DC Brent Pry as new head football coach |url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/32753004/sources-virginia-tech-hokies-zeroing-penn-state-nittany-lions-dc-brent-pry-coach |website=espn.com |publisher=ESPN |access-date=February 1, 2022}}</ref>
* On November 28, 2021, Duke head coach [[David Cutcliffe]] agreed to part ways with the program<ref>{{cite web |last1=Adelson |first1=Andrea |title=Duke, football coach David Cutcliffe mutually agree to part after 14 seasons |date=November 28, 2021|url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/32738302/duke-football-coach-david-cutcliffe-mutually-agree-part-14-seasons |website=espn.com |publisher=ESPN |access-date=February 1, 2022}}</ref> and was replaced by [[Mike Elko]] on December 10, 2021.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Rittenberg |first1=Adam |date=December 10, 2021|title=Duke hires Texas A&M defensive coordinator Mike Elko as head football coach |url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/32839321/sources-duke-hiring-texas-defensive-coordinator-mike-elko-head-football-coach |website=espn.com |publisher=ESPN |access-date=February 1, 2022}}</ref>
* On December 2, 2021, Virginia head coach [[Bronco Mendenhall]] stepped down as head coach<ref>{{cite web |last1=Adelson |first1=Andrea |title=Bronco Mendenhall to step down as Virginia Cavaliers football coach |url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/32772659/bronco-mendenhall-steps-virginia-cavaliers-football-coach |website=espn.com |publisher=ESPN |access-date=February 1, 2022|date=December 2, 2021}}</ref> and was replaced by [[Tony Elliott (American football coach)|Tony Elliott]] on December 10, 2021.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Low |first1=Chris |date=December 10, 2021|title=Virginia Cavaliers hire Clemson Tigers OC Tony Elliott as head football coach |url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/32838240/virginia-cavaliers-hire-clemson-tigers-oc-tony-elliott-head-football-coach |website=espn.com |publisher=ESPN |access-date=February 1, 2022}}</ref>
* On December 6, 2021, Miami head coach [[Manny Diaz (American football)|Manny Diaz]] was fired<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hale |first1=Davis |title=Miami Hurricanes fire football coach Manny Diaz |date=December 6, 2021 |url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/32804516/miami-hurricanes-fire-football-coach-manny-diaz |website=espn.com |publisher=ESPN |access-date=February 1, 2022}}</ref> and was replaced by [[Mario Cristobal]] on December 7, 2021.<ref>{{cite web |title=Mario Cristobal introduced as new Miami Hurricanes football coach: 'It's time to go to work' |url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/32816568/mario-cristobal-introduced-new-miami-hurricanes-football-coach-go-work |website=espn.com |publisher=ESPN |access-date=February 1, 2022|date=December 7, 2021}}</ref>

